  "title": "ASSISTANT BUILDING CONSTRUCTION ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Attend project safety meeting and site co-ordination meeting.</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure work is executed in accordance with specifications.</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor daily work progress and feedback.</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor materials delivery schedule.</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor work progress on site and ensure the project meets the schedule.     \n</li><li>Schedule and arrange site access arrangement for delivery with contractor.</li></ul><ul><li>Manage and operate all construction equipment and power hand tools.</li></ul><ul><li>Knowledge of AutoCAD is an advantage.</li></ul><ul><li>Implement variation work upon receiving new drawings and instructions.</li></ul><ul><li>Conduct follow-up site testing and viewing.</li></ul><ul><li>Coordinate with subcontractors to resolve technical issues.</li></ul><ul><li>Commissioning of project in line with main con timeline.</li></ul><ul><li>Prepare as-built drawings, operation and maintenance manual.</li></ul><ul><li>Liaise with clients and consultants on the document and drawing submission and identify any discrepancies etc.</li></ul><ul><li>Assist the SO for preparation of presentation materials as and when required.</li></ul><ul><li>Aid all processes in emergency outages and administer efficient flow of all work. </li></ul><ul><li>Candidates must possess a Diploma/bachelor’s degree in engineering (Civil, Mechanical, Electrical) or equivalent.   </li></ul><ul><li>At least 5 years of relevant experience in construction/building\nindustry.</li></ul><ul><li>Able to design and calculate the strength of the\nstructure independently.   \n</li><li>Strong Analytical and critical thinking skills\nwith high level of accuracy in calculations/design/timeline.       \n</li></ul><ul><li>Good interpersonal skills, positive attitude and\nproactivity.      \n</li></ul><ul><li>Willing to workday & night.    \n</li></ul><ul><li>To comply with the safety, policies &\nprocedures of the company/site.       \n</li></ul><ul><li>Long term commitment.      \n</li></ul><ul><li>Possesses local Class 3 license an added\nadvantage or willingness to get a license.</li></ul>",
